cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the classification of emotional relationships between fictional characters, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural methods for relation identification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the annotation of a corpus, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of social networks in literature, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
